<p><strong>Grafted Dragon</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fists" href="/Fists" target="">Fist&nbsp; </a>in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Grafted Dragon</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for dealing additional Fire Damage to foes within a wide range.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>The embodiment of the power that still remained in the dragon's head that was grafted to Godrick's left arm.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The wielder's arm will take the form of a small dragon, sprouting sharp dragon fangs at the fist.<br>This weapon cannot be two-handed.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Grafted Dragon in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Grafted Dragon weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Trade <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Remembrance of the Grafted" href="/Remembrance+of+the+Grafted">Remembrance of the Grafted</a> with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enia" href="/Enia">Enia</a> at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold">Roundtable Hold</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Grafted Dragon Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bear Witness!" href="/Bear+Witness!" target="">Bear Witness!</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Grafted Dragon</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Deals +10% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#dragon"><img title="Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Dragon</a>&nbsp;type enemies</li> 
 <li>Deals +5% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#ancient-dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#ancient-dragon"><img title="Ancient Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/ancient-dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="ancient dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Ancient Dragon</a>&nbsp;type enemies</li> 
 <li>Cannot be two-handed (weapon only contains one knuckle)</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Grafted Dragon</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Grafted Dragon Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Grafted Dragon Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
