				<li id="16721506" class="cmnt-root" data="7" data-d="1655949362000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578225/Grafted-Dragon" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">22 Jun 2022 21:56</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16721506" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This weapon seems awesome. I only tested it at +0 against the stagecoach trolls + entourage in Limgrave, as well as gateway ruins, but I had low stats. Anyway it did really well against those enemies, far better than other +0 weapons I experimented with.<br/><br/>When you activate it, you plunge your first into the ground, immediately gaining hyper-armor for yourself and also creating a pool of lava that damages and stun-locks anyone on top of it (i.e. anyone in melee range in front of you).<br/><br/>Next, you do an uppercut that seems to do very good damage and can knock people down. I knocked down the godrick knights each time I did it.<br/><br/>Finally, lots of small blobs of lava get spread around a relatively large AoE, doing relatively low damage but for a good amount of time, and each proc causes the enemies to flinch. So you can fight the enemies while they&apos;re being damaged by the lava. I was able to wipe out the entourage behind the stagecoach with just a few casts of it, purely from this lava shower.<br/><br/>So overall this gives you hyper-armor, stun-locks and/or knocks down enemies, and does great damage. Main disadvantage is it is the only fist weapon I&apos;m aware of that cannot be paired; you only have one of them. (Which makes sense lore-wise.)<br/><br/>By contrast, the Magma Wyrm Scalesword (from ruin-strewn precipice) did worse damage in a tiny area and its lava disappears after a second or two.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16721506" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16721506" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">4</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>9</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16721506"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16721506" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16721506"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16719308" class="cmnt-root" data="23" data-d="1655709129000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578225/Grafted-Dragon" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">20 Jun 2022 03:12</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16719308" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">How to turn this sock puppet into a hand held nuke:<br/><br/>- Get 99 Fth<br/>- Get Erdtree Seal +10<br/>- Grab a pleb weapon with your favourite moveset<br/>- Use Electrify Armament<br/>- Go up close to something and then use this thing&apos;s WA<br/><br/>The damage and effects of weapon buffs on your main hand, will transfer over to the WA of Grafted Dragon (Which will take priority when held in the left hand to boot). A 99 Fth Electrify Armament cast with a +10 Erdtree Seal adds 275 flat lightning damage to a weapon. Which then gets added to each fireball and tick of the fire patches from Grafted Dragon&apos;s WA leading to insane damage (Even at only +4 GD and +4 ES I managed to hit a Putrid Avatar for 3.8k with a single WA, not accounting for the remaining fire patch damage ticks)<br/><br/>For something a bit &quot;Mogh-ier&quot; you can swap Electrify Armament for Bloodflame Blade. You lose out on the raw damage (Only 147 damage compared to 275) but get a bunch of bleed build up from each hit (Including flame patch damage ticks). Throw in Fire&apos;s Deadly Sin for more buff based shenanigans (As it too will apply Bloodflame Blade&apos;s bleed build up)</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16719308" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16719308" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>27</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>4</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16719308"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16719308" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16719308"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
